Aim

To implement Linear Regression to find the relationship between input and output variables and predict values using a regression line.

Algorithm

Collect the dataset with input (X) and output (Y) values.

Import required libraries.

Split data into independent and dependent variables.

Train the Linear Regression model.

Predict output values.

Plot the regression line with data points.

Python Code
# Linear Regression Implementation

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

# Dataset
X = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]).reshape(-1, 1)
Y = np.array([2, 4, 6, 8, 10])

# Create Linear Regression model
model = LinearRegression()

# Train the model
model.fit(X, Y)

# Predict values
Y_pred = model.predict(X)

# Print results
print("Slope:", model.coef_)
print("Intercept:", model.intercept_)

# Plot graph
plt.scatter(X, Y)
plt.plot(X, Y_pred)
plt.xlabel("Input")
plt.ylabel("Output")
plt.title("Linear Regression")
plt.show()

Output
Slope: [2.]
Intercept: 0.0


(Graph showing straight line passing through data points)

Result

Thus, Linear Regression was successfully implemented and the relationship between input and output variables was identified using a straight-line graph.
